WEBVTT

00:01.784 --> 00:04.830
♪♪

00:10.836 --> 00:13.361
Walters:
Believe me when I tell you

00:13.361 --> 00:18.496
I'm making it a personal crusade
to put you behind bars.

00:18.496 --> 00:22.500
If you think
you can get away with this,

00:22.500 --> 00:24.067
you don't know me at all.

00:24.067 --> 00:27.157
I've already assigned
a new prosecutor.

00:27.157 --> 00:29.551
[ Whispering ] Male.

00:29.551 --> 00:31.857
[ Normal voice ] We're re-filing
charges against you.

00:31.857 --> 00:33.642
It'll be the case
that ends your career.

00:33.642 --> 00:36.601
You barged into my office
so you could threaten me?

00:36.601 --> 00:38.125
Well, it's not a threat.

00:38.125 --> 00:39.778
It's a fact.

00:39.778 --> 00:41.998
You just told me
I have nothing to lose.

00:41.998 --> 00:44.000
Naturally, I'll use
every tactic I know

00:44.000 --> 00:46.089
to stay a free man
as long as I can.

00:46.089 --> 00:47.873
Months of news stories

00:47.873 --> 00:49.962
about the sex scandal going on
right under your nose,

00:49.962 --> 00:51.877
and you couldn't even
smell it.

00:51.877 --> 00:54.619
Your top attorney, Alan,
your protegee,

00:54.619 --> 00:57.144
sexually involved
with the defendant?

00:59.189 --> 01:01.104
How did you
let this happen?

01:01.104 --> 01:02.410
Oh.

01:02.410 --> 01:05.413
Would you --
Do you want me to zoom in?

01:05.413 --> 01:07.719
Mm, that's not really
Melissa's best angle.

01:07.719 --> 01:10.548
Look!

01:10.548 --> 01:12.333
The two of you...

01:12.333 --> 01:13.986
are a disgrace
to the profession.

01:13.986 --> 01:16.424
You'll be begging me to plead
to a no-time misdemeanor

01:16.424 --> 01:17.773
just to take yourself
out of the news.

01:17.773 --> 01:19.079
I'll take my chances.

01:19.079 --> 01:21.124
And then,
you'll lose in court.

01:21.124 --> 01:22.821
Because Cassie
was driving the car.

01:22.821 --> 01:24.388
[ Laughs ]

01:24.388 --> 01:28.000
The number-one lie
from DUI attorneys --

01:28.000 --> 01:30.394
My client wasn't driving.

01:30.394 --> 01:32.179
I'm surprised you waited
this long to try it out.

01:32.179 --> 01:34.268
This is a no-win case
for you, Alan.

01:34.268 --> 01:35.747
You re-file against me,

01:35.747 --> 01:39.099
I will testify
that Cassie was driving the car.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.578
You file against her,

01:40.578 --> 01:42.580
she'll testify
that I was driving the car.

01:42.580 --> 01:45.017
It's a classic he-said,
she-said situation.

01:45.017 --> 01:46.149
[ Sighs ]

01:46.149 --> 01:48.804
Oh.

01:48.804 --> 01:51.633
Shame on you...

01:51.633 --> 01:54.375
for so much.

01:54.375 --> 01:56.986
[ Chuckles ]
Well...

01:56.986 --> 01:59.902
Desperate times,
desperate measures.

02:06.169 --> 02:09.694
No jury will convict me, Alan.
And you know it.

02:09.694 --> 02:12.697
We'll see.

02:12.697 --> 02:15.004
I can't save you
from yourself.

02:20.227 --> 02:23.186
[ Indistinct conversations,
elevator bell dings ]

02:23.186 --> 02:25.188
Melissa.

02:25.188 --> 02:30.802
My office, please.

02:30.802 --> 02:32.282
Tell me you're not
reconsidering.

02:32.282 --> 02:35.111
There's a lack of physical
evidence in the case.

02:35.111 --> 02:38.549
Except, of course,
for your own involvement.

02:38.549 --> 02:41.552
In a public restroom?

02:41.552 --> 02:44.947
With Siletti?

02:44.947 --> 02:48.080
I should have disclosed to you,
but I saw a winnable case.

02:48.080 --> 02:50.126
No, you saw a case

02:50.126 --> 02:52.955
that would fast-track
your career by five years.

02:52.955 --> 02:54.913
And protect yours.

02:54.913 --> 02:57.525
You wanted him
out of the way, Alan.

02:57.525 --> 03:00.267
So re-file against him
and convict him as charged.

03:00.267 --> 03:01.703
We both know he's guilty.

03:01.703 --> 03:05.881
And he's going to skate
because of you, Melissa.

03:05.881 --> 03:07.926
That's on you.

03:07.926 --> 03:10.233
If you haven't already started
cleaning out your office,

03:10.233 --> 03:13.323
you should.

03:13.323 --> 03:16.065
-You're firing me.
-No.

03:16.065 --> 03:18.285
You're resigning.

03:18.285 --> 03:22.593
I'll issue a statement on your
behalf at the end of the day.

03:22.593 --> 03:24.943
There are extra boxes
in the file room.

03:28.033 --> 03:29.818
You know...
[ Sighs ]

03:29.818 --> 03:32.124
for a pretty woman,

03:32.124 --> 03:34.823
you're not
very photogenic,

03:34.823 --> 03:36.868
especially in profile.

03:42.004 --> 03:45.050
♪♪

03:55.583 --> 03:58.020
-What's this guy's name?
-Uh, Hal Woodward.

03:58.020 --> 04:00.152
He is the barber
that led Billy James

04:00.152 --> 04:01.719
to the car
that he got murdered in.

04:01.719 --> 04:03.286
His grandson
was Billy's lawyer.

04:03.286 --> 04:04.722
-Right.
-He's a family friend,

04:04.722 --> 04:07.159
good guy, old-school.
He's the one who called us.

04:07.159 --> 04:09.510
Billy's grandma obviously wasn't
gonna come in here by herself,

04:09.510 --> 04:10.946
-so...
-He wouldn't tell you why?

04:10.946 --> 04:12.817
Unh-unh. Just that he had
to bring us something.

04:12.817 --> 04:14.689
Oh, something, anything,
is better than nothing

04:14.689 --> 04:16.081
at this point.

04:16.081 --> 04:18.040
[ Sighs ]
I hate smart criminals.

04:18.040 --> 04:19.476
-They make us work too hard.
-Yeah.

04:19.476 --> 04:21.173
Luckily, there are
so few of them.

04:21.173 --> 04:23.263
Well, they're late.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.742
They're here.

04:26.570 --> 04:28.529
Thank you.

04:28.529 --> 04:30.313
Rainelle: This, um...
[ Clears throat ]

04:30.313 --> 04:32.707
This came in the mail.

04:32.707 --> 04:34.491
It's Billy's wallet.

04:36.580 --> 04:37.973
Who sent this to you?

04:37.973 --> 04:39.583
Good Samaritan.

04:39.583 --> 04:42.282
Somebody must have found it,
dropped it in a mailbox.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.023
The post office delivered to
the address on Billy's license.

04:45.023 --> 04:47.112
There's still a few good people
left in the world.

04:47.112 --> 04:48.810
[ Chuckles ]

04:48.810 --> 04:50.246
There's a key inside

04:50.246 --> 04:52.292
that Rainelle don't know
what it's for.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.816
But I said to her,
something important,

04:54.816 --> 04:56.644
for Billy to carry it around.

04:56.644 --> 04:59.647
I said we need to bring in the
whole wallet, just like it came.

04:59.647 --> 05:02.171
-Mm-hmm.
-I-I took one thing, though.

05:02.171 --> 05:06.044
I found a tatty old photo of him
and Normandy together.

05:06.044 --> 05:08.786
So I-I kept that for myself.

05:08.786 --> 05:11.006
My two boys.

05:11.006 --> 05:13.443
[ Voice breaking ]
My two dead boys.

05:13.443 --> 05:16.490
We'll get the wallet back to you
as soon as we can, Ms. James.

05:16.490 --> 05:18.492
Thank you for bringing it in.

05:20.755 --> 05:23.584
Find out who killed my grandson,
you hear?

05:23.584 --> 05:25.237
Make sure you do that.

05:25.237 --> 05:26.543
Yes, ma'am.

05:26.543 --> 05:28.371
Thank you.

05:28.371 --> 05:30.721
[ Door opens ]

05:30.721 --> 05:32.593
Okay.

05:32.593 --> 05:34.682
Mr. Billy James.

05:34.682 --> 05:36.988
One driver's license.

05:36.988 --> 05:40.122
No credit cards or ATM.

05:40.122 --> 05:41.515
No cash.

05:41.515 --> 05:44.082
-To make it look like a robbery.
-Right.

05:44.082 --> 05:46.955
Where the hell's this key
they were talking about?

05:49.044 --> 05:50.524
Uh...

05:54.397 --> 05:56.443
Here we go.

05:56.443 --> 05:58.314
It's a safe deposit
box key.

05:58.314 --> 05:59.881
Mm-hmm.

06:11.109 --> 06:13.895
Hildy: All right, can you find
out where Billy did his banking?

06:13.895 --> 06:15.940
Ask me something hard,
why don't you?

06:15.940 --> 06:17.420
So is that a yes?

06:17.420 --> 06:18.987
I still have
all his banking records

06:18.987 --> 06:20.771
from when he was on the run.

06:20.771 --> 06:24.819
It won't tell us which branch
he used, but let's see.

06:24.819 --> 06:26.995
Here we go. The bank is
First National Pacific.

06:26.995 --> 06:29.389
How many branches
are in the Bay Area?

06:33.480 --> 06:35.743
Mm, 25.

06:35.743 --> 06:39.050
I can at least tell you
where he opened his account.

06:39.050 --> 06:40.835
All right, thanks, Keef.
You're the best.

06:40.835 --> 06:42.445
I try.

06:45.666 --> 06:47.885
[ Sniffling ]

06:52.020 --> 06:53.761
[ Chuckling ]
Inspectors!

06:53.761 --> 06:55.763
Excuse the wait.
How can I help?

06:55.763 --> 06:57.417
Terry: Uh...

06:57.417 --> 06:59.288
Sorry!
[ Sobbing ]

06:59.288 --> 07:02.117
Long night with the boyfriend.
Don't ask.

07:02.117 --> 07:03.597
Right.
Uh, Miss Gardner,

07:03.597 --> 07:05.860
uh, we're looking
to open a safe deposit box,

07:05.860 --> 07:07.818
-please?
-They say they love you,

07:07.818 --> 07:10.125
that they want
to be yours forever,

07:10.125 --> 07:11.779
but then you
go through their phone,

07:11.779 --> 07:14.346
and you see they've been texting
their ex-girlfriend.

07:14.346 --> 07:17.915
The guy doesn't even
share the rent.

07:17.915 --> 07:20.396
What is it with men?

07:20.396 --> 07:22.050
Uh...

07:22.050 --> 07:23.965
I don't know.

07:26.358 --> 07:27.882
Men can be dogs.
[ Chuckles ]

07:27.882 --> 07:31.363
But we still need you
to open up box 1220.

07:31.363 --> 07:33.365
[ Clears throat ]

07:33.365 --> 07:35.063
This isn't
from one of our boxes.

07:35.063 --> 07:37.195
Our branch doesn't use
this type of key.

07:37.195 --> 07:38.980
-What about a different branch?
-Maybe,

07:38.980 --> 07:41.156
but you need to go to each
branch and show them the key.

07:41.156 --> 07:43.114
Wait, so each branch
has a different key?

07:43.114 --> 07:45.726
Banks change names. They get
acquired by other banks.

07:45.726 --> 07:47.554
Some fold.
And when that happens,

07:47.554 --> 07:50.992
they don't reissue keys to all
their existing customers.

07:50.992 --> 07:52.776
It's too complicated.

07:52.776 --> 07:57.738
This key could be for a box
at any branch of any bank.

07:57.738 --> 08:00.044
I'm sorry.

08:00.044 --> 08:01.393
You want all the names

08:01.393 --> 08:04.571
of all the banks
in the entire Bay Area?

08:04.571 --> 08:06.181
That will be a long list.

08:06.181 --> 08:09.053
Plus the other 24 FNP branches
that we want to check out.

08:09.053 --> 08:12.404
Well, we can't canvass
every bank, so...

08:12.404 --> 08:14.494
I could run
a proximity search

08:14.494 --> 08:16.452
based on Billy's
permanent address.

08:16.452 --> 08:18.759
His grandma's house.
Yeah, do that.

08:22.458 --> 08:25.374
There are more than 75 banks
in a 5-mile radius.

08:25.374 --> 08:26.984
Okay. Well,
take a picture of the key

08:26.984 --> 08:28.203
and e-mail it
to all of them.

08:28.203 --> 08:29.857
Somebody's got
to recognize it.

08:35.166 --> 08:37.734
Tucker, McCart,
Wireman, Clay & Chang.

08:37.734 --> 08:39.997
I'll transfer.[ Telephone rings ]

08:39.997 --> 08:41.390
Tucker, McCart,
Wireman, Clay & Chang.

08:41.390 --> 08:42.783
Look at you,
you smart son of a bitch.

08:42.783 --> 08:44.175
-I'm sorry. He's not in.
-Unbelievable.

08:44.175 --> 08:45.568
-Would you like his voicemail?
-Come on.

08:45.568 --> 08:47.657
Let's go talk
in my office.

08:47.657 --> 08:51.226
Just remarkable work, the way
you played the prosecutor.

08:51.226 --> 08:52.706
Man, that was
a thing of beauty.

08:52.706 --> 08:54.882
I wouldn't call it "played,"
per se.

08:54.882 --> 08:56.361
I advised my counsel

08:56.361 --> 08:58.450
on which legal strategy
would be best follow.

08:58.450 --> 09:01.366
The photo evidence
on your phone helped.

09:01.366 --> 09:02.542
[ Chuckles ]

09:02.542 --> 09:04.195
You heard about that.

09:04.195 --> 09:06.110
There's hardly any secrets
in the Hall of Justice.

09:06.110 --> 09:08.025
She should've just let you
plead to a misdemeanor

09:08.025 --> 09:09.766
and saved
both your careers.

09:09.766 --> 09:13.074
Overreaching, man --
It's a curse.

09:13.074 --> 09:14.336
Did you just
invite me here

09:14.336 --> 09:17.121
to, uh,
pat me on the back?

09:21.865 --> 09:24.651
I convinced the executive
committee to renew our offer.

09:24.651 --> 09:25.826
You ready to change sides?

09:25.826 --> 09:28.524
[ Chuckles ]
Ah.

09:28.524 --> 09:29.830
[ Inhales ]

09:34.095 --> 09:35.226
What's this?

09:35.226 --> 09:36.619
An inducement.

09:39.274 --> 09:40.754
A signing bonus?

09:40.754 --> 09:43.495
[ Both chuckle ]You got a lot of balls, Mario.

09:43.495 --> 09:46.498
You tell the executive committee
balls cost.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.330
I'll wait here.

09:54.376 --> 09:55.551
-You don't think so?
-I don't think.

09:55.551 --> 09:57.248
-Hey.
-Hey.

09:57.248 --> 09:59.903
Hey.So I've heard from
like a dozen banks so far.

09:59.903 --> 10:01.775
Not one of them
recognizes your key,

10:01.775 --> 10:03.211
which I think is predictive.

10:03.211 --> 10:05.213
We could wait to hear back
from all of them.

10:05.213 --> 10:07.128
-Or?
-Or I could break my rule

10:07.128 --> 10:09.391
about zero communication
with an ex.

10:09.391 --> 10:10.740
To solve a double homicide?

10:10.740 --> 10:12.873
A good reason
doesn't make it easy.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.439
Sorry.

10:14.439 --> 10:17.225
Lana Decker is a master
locksmith in Berkeley.

10:17.225 --> 10:19.444
She knows everything there
is to know about keys.

10:19.444 --> 10:20.881
All right.

10:20.881 --> 10:23.057
She's also the one
that I let get away.

10:23.057 --> 10:25.581
-Hmm.
-She wanted to settle down,

10:25.581 --> 10:27.583
and I wasn't ready for her.

10:27.583 --> 10:29.672
-All about the timing, right?
-Mm-hmm.

10:29.672 --> 10:32.283
Right.

10:32.283 --> 10:34.982
Definitely a safe deposit box,
by the shape and thickness.

10:34.982 --> 10:36.897
Right, well, Kami said
she hadn't found anywhere

10:36.897 --> 10:38.376
that recognized it yet,
so...

10:38.376 --> 10:39.987
She's not perfect.

10:39.987 --> 10:42.554
[ Sighs ]
Nobody is.

10:42.554 --> 10:45.557
Personally, I'd never put
something important in a bank.

10:45.557 --> 10:47.385
Way too on the grid for me.

10:47.385 --> 10:49.431
What's the alternative?

10:49.431 --> 10:51.128
A private vault.

10:51.128 --> 10:53.653
Totally anonymous,
no SSNs on file,

10:53.653 --> 10:56.481
better security, cheaper.
What's not to like?

10:56.481 --> 10:58.048
Well, where would you find
one of these?

10:58.048 --> 11:00.311
-Are they still around?
-I know of one in Oakland

11:00.311 --> 11:02.487
that took over a chapter-11 bank
a few years back,

11:02.487 --> 11:04.272
so this type of key
would make sense.

11:04.272 --> 11:07.710
Kami said you'd know everything
there is to know about keys.

11:07.710 --> 11:09.581
She broke my heart.

11:09.581 --> 11:11.671
-Did she tell you that?
-Well, she misses you.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.150
Not enough to call me.

11:13.150 --> 11:15.631
Well, what if she did?

11:15.631 --> 11:17.111
I'd love to hear her voice.

11:17.111 --> 11:19.417
Okay.

11:19.417 --> 11:21.681
Uh, uh, sorry to interrupt.
Where can I find

11:21.681 --> 11:24.292
one of these vaults in Oakland
that you're speaking of?

11:27.948 --> 11:30.733
[ Clears throat ]

11:30.733 --> 11:32.996
They have an iris scan,
palm geometry,

11:32.996 --> 11:34.868
fingerprint reader,
full biometrics.

11:34.868 --> 11:36.913
And, apparently,
old-fashioned keys.

11:36.913 --> 11:39.307
-That's weird.
-It's not the box that matters.

11:39.307 --> 11:41.613
It's the infrastructure
around it.

11:41.613 --> 11:43.267
Ask for Janko.

11:43.267 --> 11:45.226
Maybe he'll like you.

11:47.402 --> 11:48.708
I'll tell Keefer
you said hi.

11:48.708 --> 11:50.448
-Thank you.
-Thanks.

11:57.325 --> 11:59.240
Siletti:
Final bill...

11:59.240 --> 12:00.720
Paid in full.

12:00.720 --> 12:04.071
Wouldn't want the lights
to turn off this month.

12:04.071 --> 12:06.813
You know, you could have just...
mailed it.

12:06.813 --> 12:08.684
I could have.

12:11.034 --> 12:13.036
I took a new job.

12:13.036 --> 12:14.777
Frank Tucker's firm.

12:14.777 --> 12:16.953
Signing bonus,
name on the door.

12:16.953 --> 12:19.303
Yeah, your own private toilet
with a solid-gold seat.

12:19.303 --> 12:20.827
Where are you going
with this, Mario?

12:20.827 --> 12:21.915
Are you jealous?

12:21.915 --> 12:24.352
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, bitterly.

12:24.352 --> 12:26.180
Uh-huh.Why aren't you staying on
as a D.A.?

12:26.180 --> 12:28.748
I-I thought you wanted
to, you know, clear your name,

12:28.748 --> 12:30.575
get back on
the whole political track.

12:30.575 --> 12:32.534
Well, sometimes it's best
to stop and reassess

12:32.534 --> 12:35.972
and adjust your strategy.
You know, the supreme art of war

12:35.972 --> 12:38.061
is to subdue the enemy
without fighting.

12:38.061 --> 12:40.716
[ Chuckles ]
Well, this isn't ancient China,

12:40.716 --> 12:43.197
and you ain't Sun Tsu.

12:43.197 --> 12:45.982
And there doesn't always
have to be an enemy, Mario.

12:45.982 --> 12:47.984
Therein lies the difference
between us, Al.

12:47.984 --> 12:50.726
And you did a lot of damage

12:50.726 --> 12:54.556
to save your own sorry ass.

12:54.556 --> 12:58.125
You derailed
Melissa Danson's career.

12:58.125 --> 13:01.824
You ruined
the A.G.'s reputation.

13:01.824 --> 13:04.653
And then you forced your wife
to humiliate herself

13:04.653 --> 13:07.134
in public
and on the record,

13:07.134 --> 13:09.092
and made me
look like an idiot,

13:09.092 --> 13:11.660
played by my own client.

13:14.663 --> 13:17.100
You are a shameless prick,
Mario.

13:20.800 --> 13:23.280
We do what we can
with what we have.

13:23.280 --> 13:25.239
I won.

13:25.239 --> 13:26.806
[ Chuckles ]
Well,

13:26.806 --> 13:28.808
technically, you won.

13:45.302 --> 13:47.652
Please don't ever
call me again.

13:57.488 --> 13:59.360
Oh, Mr. Siletti?

14:01.928 --> 14:04.191
Don't forget
how this all happened.

14:04.191 --> 14:05.757
It was the power
of the vision board

14:05.757 --> 14:08.804
that helped you to rise
like a phoenix.

14:08.804 --> 14:11.198
No, it wasn't.

14:16.943 --> 14:20.381
Hildy: Is this key
to one of your boxes?

14:20.381 --> 14:22.557
[ Sighs ]

14:22.557 --> 14:25.212
Maybe, maybe not.

14:25.212 --> 14:28.084
Keys can look alike.

14:28.084 --> 14:30.913
Okay, well, do you have a box
numbered 1220?

14:33.133 --> 14:34.830
People come
to the private vault

14:34.830 --> 14:37.180
because they don't
trust the banks,

14:37.180 --> 14:39.748
they don't trust the government,

14:39.748 --> 14:41.750
and they don't trust the cops.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.578
I know how they feel.

14:43.578 --> 14:45.145
Hildy:
Janko, we have reason to believe

14:45.145 --> 14:49.149
that the box-holder for this key
was a murder victim.

14:49.149 --> 14:50.498
[ Sighs ]

14:50.498 --> 14:53.240
[ Speaks Russian ]

14:53.240 --> 14:54.632
May the soul rest in peace.

14:54.632 --> 14:56.373
We're trying
to solve a homicide,

14:56.373 --> 14:58.462
not invade anyone's privacy.

14:58.462 --> 15:01.030
Terry:
Look, we can come back here
with a search warrant, okay?

15:01.030 --> 15:03.032
I don't know how good
that would be for business.

15:03.032 --> 15:05.208
And I'm guessing you wouldn't
want us to run your name

15:05.208 --> 15:07.036
though our database
just in case we found out

15:07.036 --> 15:09.647
that you were
less than a model citizen.

15:09.647 --> 15:11.084
[ Chuckles ]

15:11.084 --> 15:13.129
In my country,

15:13.129 --> 15:16.567
police threats
leave teeth on the floor.

15:16.567 --> 15:18.526
Welcome to America.

15:18.526 --> 15:20.441
[ Chuckles ]

15:20.441 --> 15:22.008
No one gets into our vault

15:22.008 --> 15:24.662
without hand scan
and fingerprint confirmation.

15:24.662 --> 15:25.881
[ Beep ]

15:25.881 --> 15:28.536
Plus iris recognition.

15:28.536 --> 15:30.364
[ Beeping ]

15:30.364 --> 15:34.020
State-of-the-art security.

15:34.020 --> 15:36.065
Sounds like an ad.

15:36.065 --> 15:38.067
It is the ad.

15:47.642 --> 15:49.339
Wait, where you going?

15:49.339 --> 15:51.341
I never look inside.

15:53.909 --> 15:55.780
All right.

15:58.914 --> 16:01.134
[ Sighs ]
See what we got.

16:06.487 --> 16:08.706
So you don't know
who rented the box.

16:08.706 --> 16:11.274
Totally anonymous.
No IDs,

16:11.274 --> 16:14.538
no Social Security numbers,
no names.

16:14.538 --> 16:17.367
Here, you're just a box number.
And we're proud of the privacy.

16:17.367 --> 16:20.066
Okay, well, privacy
ends at death, so...

16:20.066 --> 16:22.720
Okay, so when was
the last time

16:22.720 --> 16:25.810
"Box Number 1220"
entered the vault?

16:29.553 --> 16:31.338
[ Sighs ]

16:34.384 --> 16:39.259
May 17th.

16:39.259 --> 16:42.175
Okay.
Thanks for your cooperation.

16:42.175 --> 16:45.221
America --
land of the free.

16:45.221 --> 16:47.745
[ Chuckles ]

16:47.745 --> 16:49.356
My ass.

16:52.968 --> 16:55.536
All right, so,
Billy accessed the box

16:55.536 --> 16:57.712
the afternoon
that Normandy was murdered.

16:57.712 --> 16:58.843
That was May 17.

16:58.843 --> 17:00.236
And took out
whatever was in that.

17:00.236 --> 17:01.846
-'Cause otherwise, why go?
-Exactly.

17:01.846 --> 17:03.848
-The cash when we grabbed him?
-The gun?

17:03.848 --> 17:05.111
-Or both?
-Or something else.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.895
That wasn't on him
at booking.

17:06.895 --> 17:08.897
-Something he his somewhere?
-Or gave someone.

17:08.897 --> 17:11.769
Who'd Billy see between killing
Normandy and getting killed?

17:11.769 --> 17:13.597
-His grandma.
-The barber.

17:13.597 --> 17:16.774
Ooh, his lawyer -- the barber's
grandson, Nathan Woodward.

17:16.774 --> 17:19.342
Remember, he was at
the press conference with Billy.

17:19.342 --> 17:23.564
He said, "Innocence doesn't keep
black men alive in America."

17:23.564 --> 17:25.522
-Mm.
-Referring to me.

17:25.522 --> 17:28.830
Mm, Yeah, 2623 Grand Avenue,
Oakland,

17:28.830 --> 17:30.353
in case you want to hit it.[ Cellphone rings ]

17:30.353 --> 17:33.139
Inspector Mulligan.

17:33.139 --> 17:35.706
Yeah.
Louise is my daughter.

17:35.706 --> 17:39.014
What?

17:39.014 --> 17:41.364
Okay, I'll, uh -- I'll come
pick her up right now.

17:41.364 --> 17:43.323
Thanks.
I appreciate the call, officer.

17:43.323 --> 17:44.933
What's up?
Everything okay?

17:44.933 --> 17:47.283
No, not really. Instead of
going to summer school today,

17:47.283 --> 17:50.547
Louise decided to go shoplift
makeup with her friends.

17:50.547 --> 17:53.028
She's down at C.A.R.C.
being processed right now.

17:53.028 --> 17:54.421
Oh, I'm sorry.

17:54.421 --> 17:56.292
She's turning into me
when I was her age.

17:56.292 --> 18:00.818
Angry kid with an attitude,
making the same mistakes I did.

18:00.818 --> 18:03.734
Hey, I'll take care of Woodward.
You go take care of Louise.

18:03.734 --> 18:04.996
All right.
Thank you.

18:04.996 --> 18:06.389
Yep.

18:08.783 --> 18:10.132
Where's my mom?

18:10.132 --> 18:13.962
She'll be here.

18:13.962 --> 18:16.399
-All right, Louise, let's go.
-I can go?

18:16.399 --> 18:18.532
Yeah, you're lucky I didn't
make you wait here all night.

18:18.532 --> 18:20.011
I didn't
steal anything, Mom.

18:20.011 --> 18:22.623
I don't want to hear it.
Get your stuff. Let's go.

18:22.623 --> 18:25.539
-It was Sophie's idea!
-[ Sighs ]

18:25.539 --> 18:27.323
All I did was talk
to the sales lady.

18:27.323 --> 18:29.325
Sophie and Sarah
took the makeup!

18:29.325 --> 18:32.023
-Stop moving your lips.
-If your mom weren't a cop,

18:32.023 --> 18:33.982
there'd be charges
against all of you.

18:33.982 --> 18:36.506
-Do you understand?
-We're only 12!

18:36.506 --> 18:39.074
Mm-hmm. Old enough
to make bad decisions.

18:39.074 --> 18:41.598
-Thank you, Nanette.
-[ Sighs ]

18:44.079 --> 18:46.473
[ Sighs ]
You have kids, Roberts?

18:46.473 --> 18:47.648
Not yet.

18:47.648 --> 18:49.476
Well, don't rush it.

18:49.476 --> 18:50.868
I hear that.

18:50.868 --> 18:53.784
I hope I never see you again,
Louise.

18:57.353 --> 18:58.833
-Mom, I didn't steal --
-Stop.

18:58.833 --> 19:01.096
You're a thief,
and I'm ashamed of you.

19:10.975 --> 19:13.978
It's a very simple question,
Mr. Woodward.

19:13.978 --> 19:15.502
Did Billy James
give you anything

19:15.502 --> 19:17.547
between May 17th
and the day he was murdered?

19:17.547 --> 19:20.289
I can't answer that.
Attorney-client privilege.

19:20.289 --> 19:22.030
Well, your client
is dead and buried.

19:22.030 --> 19:23.379
Privilege survives death.

19:23.379 --> 19:24.902
Swidler and Berlin
v. United States.

19:24.902 --> 19:26.513
Okay, that's fine,

19:26.513 --> 19:29.080
but I have two open homicides
I'm trying to solve here.

19:29.080 --> 19:30.908
Lizzie Borden took an axe

19:30.908 --> 19:32.910
and gave her mother
40 whacks.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.564
And when she saw
what she had done,

19:34.564 --> 19:37.741
she gave her father 41...

19:37.741 --> 19:40.788
in 1892.
And her attorney's law firm

19:40.788 --> 19:44.835
is still protecting her files
as confidential to this day.

19:44.835 --> 19:48.535
Client's dead, attorney's dead,
privilege lives on.

19:48.535 --> 19:51.320
Look, Billy was your friend
way before he was a client,

19:51.320 --> 19:54.889
way before you even thought
about being a lawyer, so...

19:54.889 --> 19:56.456
Look, I know
he gave you something,

19:56.456 --> 19:58.240
or you wouldn't
be reciting nursery rhymes.

19:58.240 --> 19:59.633
You just would have said no.

19:59.633 --> 20:02.331
You're entitled to your opinion,
Inspector.

20:02.331 --> 20:05.508
That's all it is.

20:05.508 --> 20:07.467
Are we finished?

20:09.469 --> 20:13.255
No wonder
everybody hates lawyers.

20:13.255 --> 20:15.605
Not as much
as they hate cops.

20:21.611 --> 20:22.960
All right.
So sit down

20:22.960 --> 20:24.571
and do your homework
for tomorrow, okay?

20:24.571 --> 20:26.399
-What if I have to pee?
-Well, knock on the door.

20:26.399 --> 20:28.357
Maybe someone will hear you.
I got to go back to work.

20:28.357 --> 20:30.011
You're locking me in here?

20:30.011 --> 20:31.708
Look, think about it as jail

20:31.708 --> 20:33.188
without the juvenile record,
okay?

20:33.188 --> 20:34.668
You don't even want
to hear my side?

20:34.668 --> 20:35.712
I've heard enough.

20:35.712 --> 20:37.671
Ugh![ Door shuts ]

20:40.151 --> 20:41.675
[ Telephone rings ]

20:41.675 --> 20:44.504
[ Speaking Spanish ]

20:44.504 --> 20:46.070
Reyes Law,
personal injury attorneys.

20:46.070 --> 20:49.160
If you don't win,
you don't pay.

20:49.160 --> 20:52.163
Mr. Siletti,
Manuel Reyes, come on in.

20:52.163 --> 20:55.776
Ana.
[ Speaks Spanish ]

20:55.776 --> 20:57.865
[ Ana speaking Spanish ]

21:07.266 --> 21:09.006
It's impressive.

21:09.006 --> 21:11.705
Thank you.

21:11.705 --> 21:14.360
Oh, you can put your pen down,
Mr. Reyes.

21:14.360 --> 21:16.057
I didn't come here
to negotiate.

21:16.057 --> 21:19.495
Mr. Ramirez will not be getting
his picture on your wall.

21:21.541 --> 21:23.499
Your mistrial
doesn't affect our lawsuit.

21:23.499 --> 21:25.022
Well, the A.G.'s office

21:25.022 --> 21:27.503
has decided not to re-file
charges against me.

21:27.503 --> 21:29.549
And O.J. was acquitted.
So?

21:29.549 --> 21:33.292
-The civil jury got it right.
-Well, O.J. was a U.S. citizen.

21:33.292 --> 21:36.251
Your client snuck across
the border 15 years ago.

21:36.251 --> 21:37.818
He has been using fake names

21:37.818 --> 21:40.255
and fake Social Security numbers
ever since

21:40.255 --> 21:43.780
to take jobs away from people
who respect and obey the law,

21:43.780 --> 21:46.435
when he bothers
working at all.

21:46.435 --> 21:49.569
San Francisco
is a sanctuary city.

21:49.569 --> 21:54.095
And that won't protect
Mr. Ramirez from federal action.

21:54.095 --> 21:56.402
Here's how I see it.

21:56.402 --> 22:00.536
Option "A," your client drops
the civil suit against me,

22:00.536 --> 22:02.582
and life goes on
as he knows it.

22:02.582 --> 22:04.758
Option "B,"
my friends at I.C.E.

22:04.758 --> 22:09.110
somehow learn of your client's
undocumented status.

22:09.110 --> 22:12.418
Option "B"
doesn't end well for him.

22:12.418 --> 22:13.854
[ Exhales sharply ]

22:13.854 --> 22:15.551
This is extortion.

22:15.551 --> 22:17.161
I came here
as a professional courtesy.

22:17.161 --> 22:19.381
I didn't have to tell you.

22:19.381 --> 22:21.818
Now, I'm sorry about
the "no gana, no paga."

22:21.818 --> 22:23.254
But you've done
well for yourself.

22:23.254 --> 22:25.256
What's that,
1/3 of every pay out?

22:25.256 --> 22:26.432
I'll confer with my client.

22:26.432 --> 22:28.085
His children
just lost their mother.

22:28.085 --> 22:29.609
Don't let him
make this worse

22:29.609 --> 22:31.132
by costing them
their father, too.

22:31.132 --> 22:33.961
You can walk
yourself out, sir.

22:41.272 --> 22:43.536
Leverage isn't extortion.

22:43.536 --> 22:46.365
Or every case in every court
would go to trial.

22:48.715 --> 22:51.195
[ Door opens, shuts ]

22:54.547 --> 22:56.157
[ Terry sighs ]

22:56.157 --> 22:59.073
Nathan Woodward's got a secret
he's not telling.

22:59.073 --> 23:02.685
There's no way
we can force him.

23:02.685 --> 23:04.078
Wait, did you
take Louise home?

23:04.078 --> 23:05.862
I locked her
in an interrogation room.

23:05.862 --> 23:07.342
[ Chuckles ]

23:07.342 --> 23:08.691
-Wait, what?
-[ Chuckles ]

23:08.691 --> 23:10.563
Well, I couldn't
leave her at home alone.

23:10.563 --> 23:13.000
I wasn't gonna call my parents.
I couldn't find a babysitter.

23:13.000 --> 23:15.655
So at least I know if she's
in there, she's safe, right?

23:15.655 --> 23:18.571
Okay, uh...

23:18.571 --> 23:20.573
Do you mind
if I talk to her?

23:20.573 --> 23:22.052
Go ahead.
Feel my pain.

23:22.052 --> 23:23.314
-You sure?
-Do it.

23:23.314 --> 23:25.186
Okay.

23:25.186 --> 23:27.841
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:32.323 --> 23:34.238
How we doing, Lou?

23:34.238 --> 23:36.719
How do you stand her?
She's such a bitch.

23:36.719 --> 23:38.808
Ooh, easy, easy.

23:38.808 --> 23:41.594
[ Sighs ]

23:41.594 --> 23:44.161
You know she loves you, right?
She's just, uh...

23:44.161 --> 23:45.685
She just worries about you.

23:45.685 --> 23:48.383
She just worries
that I'll mess up her schedule.

23:48.383 --> 23:50.037
I try to stay out of her way.

23:50.037 --> 23:52.648
You do?

23:52.648 --> 23:54.868
Like to-- uh, like today?

23:54.868 --> 23:56.391
I knew you'd take her side.

23:56.391 --> 23:59.786
I don't want to talk to you.

23:59.786 --> 24:01.396
Okay.

24:04.704 --> 24:06.575
Where are you going?

24:08.577 --> 24:09.839
[ Door shuts ]

24:09.839 --> 24:11.145
[ Sighs ]

24:11.145 --> 24:14.104
[ Knock on door ]

24:14.104 --> 24:16.237
We have nothing new
to talk about, Mario.

24:16.237 --> 24:17.934
Well, you're wrong.

24:19.936 --> 24:21.808
I just came
from the Mayor's office,

24:21.808 --> 24:23.418
where I strongly recommended

24:23.418 --> 24:27.422
that you continue as acting D.A.
until the next election.

24:27.422 --> 24:30.381
He agreed.

24:30.381 --> 24:31.948
Well, that wasn't
necessary.

24:31.948 --> 24:33.602
You're welcome.

24:33.602 --> 24:35.212
So why would you
do this for me?

24:35.212 --> 24:37.476
I just -- I-I think you're
the right attorney for the job,

24:37.476 --> 24:40.696
Marty.
I respect you.

24:40.696 --> 24:42.872
I appreciate your testimony
for me.

24:42.872 --> 24:46.659
You know, one good turn
deserves another.

24:46.659 --> 24:48.530
No.

24:48.530 --> 24:50.880
You're thinking this will buy
juice for your future clients

24:50.880 --> 24:53.317
for when you start working
the other side of the aisle.

24:53.317 --> 24:54.580
Sorry.

24:54.580 --> 24:57.321
Not from me,
not from this office.

24:57.321 --> 24:58.975
Of course not!

25:01.848 --> 25:04.720
Congratulations, Marty.

25:04.720 --> 25:06.940
I'll see you in court.

25:13.686 --> 25:15.862
[ Sighs ][ Door shuts ]

25:29.092 --> 25:31.094
So how long you planning on
leaving, uh, Louise

25:31.094 --> 25:33.096
in the interrogation room?

25:33.096 --> 25:36.883
Hmm, till the end of the day,
when I'm ready to go home.

25:36.883 --> 25:38.972
-No food?
-She won't starve to death.

25:38.972 --> 25:40.669
[ Chuckles ]
Well, is it cool

25:40.669 --> 25:43.063
if I bring her a sandwich
from the machine?

25:43.063 --> 25:45.108
[ Sighs ]

25:45.108 --> 25:48.503
All right.
Well, she hates mustard.

25:48.503 --> 25:49.939
What if I bring her with me

25:49.939 --> 25:52.246
and let her choose
what she wants to eat?

25:54.422 --> 25:56.511
All right, and then you can
let her use the restroom.

25:56.511 --> 25:57.991
-[ Chuckles ]
-Once.

25:57.991 --> 25:59.732
Yeah, you're tough.

25:59.732 --> 26:03.649
Mm.
Obviously not tough enough.

26:03.649 --> 26:05.520
I tried to tell her
it wasn't my idea,

26:05.520 --> 26:09.480
but she doesn't
want to hear it.

26:09.480 --> 26:11.308
Okay, well, I do.

26:11.308 --> 26:13.702
Why don't you tell me?

26:13.702 --> 26:17.097
-[ Sighs ]
-Okay.

26:17.097 --> 26:19.012
I was hanging out
with Sophie and Sarah.

26:19.012 --> 26:21.580
I'm not supposed to see Sophie
because I borrowed her vape,

26:21.580 --> 26:23.407
and my mom found it in my bag.

26:23.407 --> 26:25.235
-Mm.
-E-smoke isn't like smoking.

26:25.235 --> 26:26.628
I know, right?

26:26.628 --> 26:28.891
I mean, well, except for
the nicotine, but...

26:28.891 --> 26:31.328
Go ahead, go ahead. You guys are
hanging out together, and...?

26:31.328 --> 26:33.679
And we decided
to go shopping.

26:33.679 --> 26:36.682
We were gonna pay for the stuff,
but then we didn't.

26:36.682 --> 26:39.336
Mm-hmm. Oh.
How come?

26:39.336 --> 26:41.774
I don't know.
I was talking to the sales lady

26:41.774 --> 26:43.950
about how to, like,
put on eye makeup

26:43.950 --> 26:45.995
-'cause my mom won't show me.
-Right.

26:45.995 --> 26:49.042
And then we kind of just,
you know, left.

26:49.042 --> 26:53.655
Right. So was it your job
to distract the sales lady?

26:53.655 --> 26:54.874
Maybe.

26:54.874 --> 26:56.658
But it wasn't,
like, my idea.

26:56.658 --> 26:59.226
No, no, you were just
kind of going along, right?

26:59.226 --> 27:02.185
[ Sighs ] My mom thinks
I'm a pain in the ass.

27:02.185 --> 27:03.926
Well, you are.

27:03.926 --> 27:06.407
[ Chuckles ]
I mean, so was I.

27:06.407 --> 27:08.104
-So was I.
-Yeah, right.

27:08.104 --> 27:11.020
No, for real.
Yeah, I was just about your age

27:11.020 --> 27:13.414
when I started
looking for trouble.

27:13.414 --> 27:15.459
Ah, yeah.

27:15.459 --> 27:17.200
[ Sighing ]
I got bad grades.

27:17.200 --> 27:19.376
Chose bad friends.

27:19.376 --> 27:21.814
I think I actually
held the record

27:21.814 --> 27:24.338
for the most detentions
back in the day.

27:24.338 --> 27:25.861
-[ Chuckles ]
-What for?

27:25.861 --> 27:28.211
Oh, man.
Mouthing off,

27:28.211 --> 27:30.823
cutting class --
everything.

27:30.823 --> 27:33.216
-You cut class?
-Mm-hmm!

27:33.216 --> 27:36.263
Yeah, I cut class, a lot.

27:36.263 --> 27:39.092
It was cool,
but also scary.

27:39.092 --> 27:43.574
It...
made me feel free, you know?

27:43.574 --> 27:45.446
Then some of the older kids
saw me,

27:45.446 --> 27:48.449
asked me to run with them,
join their set.

27:48.449 --> 27:51.582
It was real exciting
until...

27:51.582 --> 27:54.150
they asked me to prove
how down I was.

27:54.150 --> 27:56.936
You know, and they asked me
to do stuff I didn't like.

27:56.936 --> 27:58.328
What?

27:58.328 --> 28:01.941
Well, they asked me
to jack somebody.

28:01.941 --> 28:04.900
Did you?

28:04.900 --> 28:06.380
What do you think?

28:06.380 --> 28:08.687
I don't think so.

28:08.687 --> 28:11.080
No, you're right.

28:11.080 --> 28:13.604
Only because...

28:13.604 --> 28:16.564
I heard this little voice
in my head

28:16.564 --> 28:18.784
that told me
I was about to -- to go down

28:18.784 --> 28:22.918
a wrong-way, one-way road.

28:22.918 --> 28:25.660
And that voice
belonged to my mom.

28:25.660 --> 28:28.968
She raised me all on her own,
just like your mom.

28:28.968 --> 28:30.621
Man, was she strict.

28:30.621 --> 28:31.884
I couldn't do anything.

28:31.884 --> 28:33.494
This, that,
couldn't go anywhere.

28:33.494 --> 28:34.930
[ Chuckles ]

28:34.930 --> 28:37.628
She was the meanest mom
on the block...

28:37.628 --> 28:40.675
but she was the best.

28:40.675 --> 28:42.721
Because she cared.

28:45.462 --> 28:46.942
Well...

28:46.942 --> 28:49.597
I miss her every day.
[ Clears throat ]

28:49.597 --> 28:52.208
-Oh.
-[ Sniffs ]

28:52.208 --> 28:54.167
I was 18.

28:54.167 --> 28:56.560
[ Chuckles ]
It was a long time ago.

28:56.560 --> 28:58.388
Who took care of you?

28:58.388 --> 29:01.261
Who t-- uh, Uncle Sam.

29:01.261 --> 29:03.785
The Army.

29:03.785 --> 29:08.398
The Army made sure
I was right.

29:08.398 --> 29:12.576
So...
[ Clears throat ]

29:12.576 --> 29:17.146
Listen to your mom's voice
in your head, all right?

29:17.146 --> 29:19.061
She knows her shit.

29:24.066 --> 29:26.634
When's she gonna
take me home?

29:31.073 --> 29:33.641
Soon, all right?

29:33.641 --> 29:35.382
Here, eat.

29:38.777 --> 29:40.387
How'd it go?

29:40.387 --> 29:43.129
[ Chuckles ] She's, uh --
She's ready to leave.

29:43.129 --> 29:44.870
[ Chuckles ]

29:44.870 --> 29:47.655
I'm not looking forward to the
fight we're gonna have to have.

29:47.655 --> 29:49.135
She's a good kid, Hildy.

29:49.135 --> 29:51.702
Mm, she scares me to death.

29:51.702 --> 29:53.226
We used to be best friends.

29:53.226 --> 29:56.882
Now I feel like I'm a cop,
even when I'm off-duty.

29:56.882 --> 29:59.536
All right. What do you want
to do about Nathan Woodward?

29:59.536 --> 30:01.669
Okay, I got, uh -- I got
one play for tomorrow,

30:01.669 --> 30:05.325
but it's a long-shot,
so...

30:05.325 --> 30:06.848
Why don't you
take Louise home?

30:06.848 --> 30:08.894
I'll finish up
all this paperwork.

30:08.894 --> 30:10.678
-Are you sure?
-Yeah, I'm good.

30:10.678 --> 30:13.637
-Have a good night.
-All right.

30:13.637 --> 30:15.596
Don't work too late.

30:15.596 --> 30:16.902
Okay.

30:34.310 --> 30:35.790
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

30:35.790 --> 30:38.837
I told you no phone,
no iPad for a week, okay?

30:38.837 --> 30:40.534
How am I supposed
to do homework?

30:40.534 --> 30:45.147
By actually doing your homework,
not Googling the answers.

30:45.147 --> 30:47.019
Louise?!

30:49.325 --> 30:52.676
[ Scoffs ]
Facebook is not homework, okay?

30:52.676 --> 30:54.287
God, you can't stop lying.

30:54.287 --> 30:57.072
-Neither can you!
-What is that supposed to mean?

30:57.072 --> 30:58.595
I know about you and Terry.

30:58.595 --> 31:01.337
He's not just your partner,
he's your boyfriend!

31:01.337 --> 31:03.949
You have sex!

31:03.949 --> 31:06.429
Louise!

31:06.429 --> 31:07.866
[ Door slams ]

31:11.391 --> 31:13.219
Go away.

31:16.091 --> 31:18.441
Why did you say that
about Terry?

31:18.441 --> 31:20.922
-I'm not stupid.
-I know you're not.

31:20.922 --> 31:23.751
It's just so totally obvious
about you and him.

31:23.751 --> 31:25.884
I mean, who gives a kid
an iPad

31:25.884 --> 31:29.757
unless he's got something going
with her mom?

31:29.757 --> 31:31.890
How do you feel
about that?

31:34.022 --> 31:36.372
I know you and Dad
are a bad idea.

31:36.372 --> 31:38.026
Honey, you are
the only thing

31:38.026 --> 31:40.550
that your dad and I
ever got right.

31:40.550 --> 31:42.901
I'm grateful to him
for you.

31:45.555 --> 31:49.037
So...
Do you love Terry?

31:51.170 --> 31:53.041
Yeah, I do.

31:53.041 --> 31:55.652
But we're not together
like that anymore.

31:55.652 --> 31:58.307
You broke up already?

31:58.307 --> 31:59.743
No. We're still friends.

31:59.743 --> 32:01.789
We're still partners.

32:01.789 --> 32:04.009
It's just...

32:04.009 --> 32:06.620
not more than that.

32:06.620 --> 32:09.188
Too bad.

32:09.188 --> 32:11.277
Why, you like him?

32:11.277 --> 32:12.843
Yeah.

32:12.843 --> 32:14.933
I feel like he gets me.

32:16.891 --> 32:19.807
And I don't?

32:19.807 --> 32:21.243
Thanks a lot.

32:21.243 --> 32:23.637
No, it's just
Terry doesn't treat me

32:23.637 --> 32:27.075
like I'm still a little kid,
and I'm not, Mom.

32:29.121 --> 32:31.123
Okay.

32:31.123 --> 32:32.907
What happened?

32:32.907 --> 32:36.519
With us?

32:36.519 --> 32:39.827
Um...

32:39.827 --> 32:42.308
Well, we wanted
to be together.

32:42.308 --> 32:44.440
But sometimes

32:44.440 --> 32:47.139
life doesn't care
about what you want,

32:47.139 --> 32:49.010
you know?

32:49.010 --> 32:53.493
And making the right choice
can be really hard,

32:53.493 --> 32:56.104
like you found out today when
your friends talked you into

32:56.104 --> 32:57.888
stealing from that store,
right?

32:57.888 --> 32:59.673
-Mom...
-I know, I know.

32:59.673 --> 33:01.980
We agreed in the car, we're not
gonna talk about it anymore.

33:01.980 --> 33:03.329
It's fine.

33:03.329 --> 33:05.984
I didn't tell you the truth
in the car.

33:08.203 --> 33:10.510
What do you mean?

33:10.510 --> 33:12.642
[ Sighs ]
They didn't talk me into it.

33:12.642 --> 33:15.123
It was my idea.
I planned it.

33:17.691 --> 33:19.301
Why?

33:19.301 --> 33:21.564
To see if they'd do it.

33:23.740 --> 33:27.701
So you put
all your friends at risk?

33:27.701 --> 33:31.096
Well, you fixed things.

33:31.096 --> 33:34.795
So that was
your backup plan?

33:34.795 --> 33:38.625
That I would
get you out of it?

33:38.625 --> 33:40.148
[ Sighs ]

33:40.148 --> 33:42.150
God, you're breaking
my heart here, Louise.

33:42.150 --> 33:45.110
I'm sorry.
I-I'm so sorry, Mom.

33:45.110 --> 33:46.415
How am I supposed
to believe you?

33:46.415 --> 33:48.200
Because it's true.

33:48.200 --> 33:50.202
I didn't have
to tell you the truth.

33:50.202 --> 33:52.291
I could have just kept lying.

33:52.291 --> 33:54.641
[ Crying ] But I'm trying
to do what's right.

33:54.641 --> 33:57.122
[ Crying ]

33:57.122 --> 33:59.124
Okay.
Okay, come here.

33:59.124 --> 34:01.126
-[ Sobbing ]
-I know you are,

34:01.126 --> 34:03.258
all right?
I know you are.

34:10.613 --> 34:13.007
Victor: So you and the wife just
sit there, not saying a word?

34:13.007 --> 34:14.182
We just sit there.

34:14.182 --> 34:16.402
[ Laughs ]
Since when?

34:16.402 --> 34:18.621
Since right after
our youngest moved out.

34:18.621 --> 34:20.101
Been months now.

34:20.101 --> 34:23.583
You've got the empty-nest blues,
my man.

34:23.583 --> 34:25.454
Happens to the best of us.

34:25.454 --> 34:26.977
Uh, what do we do?

34:26.977 --> 34:28.849
Start over again
with each other.

34:28.849 --> 34:30.503
You know,
pay attention to her.

34:30.503 --> 34:32.809
[ Chuckles ]
I acted like that,

34:32.809 --> 34:35.334
she'd just think I got something
going on on the side.

34:35.334 --> 34:37.466
No, no. Not happening.Well, maybe you should
get yourself

34:37.466 --> 34:39.468
a little something
on the side.Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

34:39.468 --> 34:41.427
-Trying to get me killed?
-Don't say that to him.

34:41.427 --> 34:44.212
-No, don't put that in his mind.
-I'm trying to help him!

34:47.172 --> 34:50.436
Morning, fellas.
Mr. Woodward.

34:50.436 --> 34:52.568
Morning. Um...

34:52.568 --> 34:54.483
What can I do for you,
Inspector?

34:54.483 --> 34:57.530
Uh, do you mind
if I take you out for breakfast?

35:01.534 --> 35:03.057
Terry:
Did you hear about the, uh --

35:03.057 --> 35:05.364
the tribute that they're doing
for Normandy?

35:05.364 --> 35:07.322
I read about it in the paper
last week.

35:07.322 --> 35:09.672
[ Chuckles ] Like a memorial
patch on a jersey

35:09.672 --> 35:11.065
does a damn thing.

35:11.065 --> 35:12.545
Yeah, well, you know...

35:12.545 --> 35:13.981
It's a way
to keep the spirit alive.

35:13.981 --> 35:16.331
It's a way for them
to sell more jerseys.

35:16.331 --> 35:18.464
They make money
even off the dead.

35:18.464 --> 35:21.162
-Mm.
-But...

35:21.162 --> 35:23.730
You're not buying my breakfast
to talk about the NFL.

35:23.730 --> 35:24.992
-Oh, no.
-No, sir, I'm not.

35:24.992 --> 35:26.646
We actually --
We need your help.

35:26.646 --> 35:28.300
[ Chuckles ]

35:28.300 --> 35:29.910
I can't tell you
what I don't know.

35:29.910 --> 35:32.260
Well, your grandson,
we think he may have

35:32.260 --> 35:34.654
some information
that could lead us to...

35:34.654 --> 35:36.264
to Billy's killer.

35:36.264 --> 35:39.093
Then you should be having
breakfast with him.

35:39.093 --> 35:42.749
As you know, it goes against
his principles to, uh...

35:42.749 --> 35:44.968
to cooperate
with the police.

35:44.968 --> 35:47.406
[ Laughing ]

35:47.406 --> 35:50.452
So you -- you want me
to lean on my grandson

35:50.452 --> 35:53.238
in exchange for a biscuit
and a couple of eggs?

35:53.238 --> 35:55.022
-Come on, man!
-Well, when you put it

35:55.022 --> 35:56.850
-like that...
-[ Chuckling ] Yeah, yeah.

35:56.850 --> 35:58.504
Yes.[ Both laugh ]

35:58.504 --> 36:01.028
Oh, wow. What kind of budget
they give you down there?

36:01.028 --> 36:02.682
Oh, man,
you're killing me.

36:02.682 --> 36:04.684
Well, I figure
we all have, uh --

36:04.684 --> 36:08.166
We all have something in common,
you, me, and him.

36:08.166 --> 36:10.994
We care about the truth.

36:10.994 --> 36:14.433
You know,
w-whatever it may be.

36:18.045 --> 36:20.961
[ Sighs ]

36:20.961 --> 36:23.006
I could walk you in.

36:24.747 --> 36:27.837
You are something shameless,
using him like this.

36:27.837 --> 36:30.362
To try to manipulate me
into violating legal ethics.

36:30.362 --> 36:33.060
I'm sitting
right here, Nathan.

36:33.060 --> 36:36.324
Don't talk around me
like I'm an old fool.

36:36.324 --> 36:40.589
If you could be of any help, you
owe it to Rainelle to speak up.

36:40.589 --> 36:42.330
That woman's been feeding you
every Sunday

36:42.330 --> 36:43.766
since you were old enough
to walk.

36:43.766 --> 36:45.768
Rainelle understands
who this man is.

36:45.768 --> 36:47.379
He shot an unarmed
brother dead.

36:47.379 --> 36:50.991
I'm not trying to change
your mind about the police.

36:50.991 --> 36:52.906
But this is personal.

36:52.906 --> 36:56.083
Whatever Billy did
is already over and done.

36:56.083 --> 36:58.477
And God will handle him.

36:58.477 --> 37:00.827
What was done
toBilly, though,

37:00.827 --> 37:03.612
that's on this side
of the compass.

37:03.612 --> 37:05.875
Any way you can help
find his killer,

37:05.875 --> 37:07.442
you owe it to Rainelle,

37:07.442 --> 37:09.749
and to Billy.

37:09.749 --> 37:11.272
You hearing me?

37:14.319 --> 37:17.539
The truth
will set you free?

37:17.539 --> 37:21.151
You could do worse
than quote the Bible.

37:21.151 --> 37:23.371
You know what's right.

37:41.215 --> 37:43.957
This came in the mail the day
after Normandy was killed.

37:50.529 --> 37:54.141
"From Billy James,
to Billy James.

37:54.141 --> 37:56.099
Care of Nathan Woodward."

37:56.099 --> 37:58.928
It's a federal offense
to open someone else's mail.

37:58.928 --> 38:01.148
I locked it in a file cabinet
for safekeeping.

38:01.148 --> 38:03.106
After Billy was arrested,

38:03.106 --> 38:05.805
he instructed me
to hold onto it for him.You know what's inside?

38:05.805 --> 38:10.113
I didn't ask him,
and he didn't tell me.

38:10.113 --> 38:13.029
Thank you, Mr. Woodward.

38:13.029 --> 38:15.162
Thank my grandfather.

38:21.124 --> 38:24.519
Hey, so, Nathan Woodward
changed his mind.

38:24.519 --> 38:26.478
Oh, you miracle worker.

38:26.478 --> 38:28.436
Well, it doesn't feel
heavy enough to be a weapon.

38:28.436 --> 38:29.872
-Mnh-mnh.
-Let's see what's inside.

38:29.872 --> 38:31.787
Yeah.

38:31.787 --> 38:33.702
Hey, did you say something
to Louise about us?

38:33.702 --> 38:35.356
What?
No, of course not.

38:35.356 --> 38:37.489
Okay, 'cause she threw it
in my face last night, so...

38:37.489 --> 38:39.273
How could she ever know
something like that?

38:39.273 --> 38:41.580
iPad. Kids are smarter
than they look.

38:41.580 --> 38:43.321
Well, how does she feel?

38:43.321 --> 38:44.626
Just sad it's over.

38:44.626 --> 38:46.585
Well, so am I.

38:54.680 --> 38:56.464
Okay. Jesus.

38:56.464 --> 38:58.118
It's like an Egyptian mummy.

38:58.118 --> 38:59.554
Mm.

39:04.298 --> 39:05.430
Okay.

39:05.430 --> 39:07.214
Mm, power it up.

39:07.214 --> 39:09.129
[ Sighs ]

39:12.828 --> 39:14.395
Nothing.

39:14.395 --> 39:16.615
It's out of juice.

39:16.615 --> 39:18.225
We need Keefer.

39:18.225 --> 39:20.619
Hey, thanks for putting in
a good word for me with Lana.

39:20.619 --> 39:22.185
Mm, hope I didn't
overstep.

39:22.185 --> 39:24.492
We have a date this weekend.
Who knows?

39:24.492 --> 39:27.669
So, this phone is protected
by a six-digit passcode.

39:27.669 --> 39:29.541
1 million possible
combinations,

39:29.541 --> 39:31.499
instead of 10,000
like the four-digit version,

39:31.499 --> 39:32.805
which would have been
bad enough.

39:32.805 --> 39:35.677
Right, but you can
do anything, so...

39:35.677 --> 39:39.812
Does this look like NSA,
CIA, DOD, FBI resources?

39:39.812 --> 39:41.335
Here's why flattery fails.

39:41.335 --> 39:44.077
If I enter the wrong passcode
10 consecutive times,

39:44.077 --> 39:46.296
the phone permanently erases
all of its data,

39:46.296 --> 39:49.430
making it a $400 paperweight
as far as you're concerned.

39:49.430 --> 39:51.867
Right, but why can't we recreate
Billy's fingerprint

39:51.867 --> 39:53.739
to unlock the touch pad,

39:53.739 --> 39:56.785
I mean, using his records and a
3-D printer? Wouldn't that work?

39:56.785 --> 39:59.048
Sure, except once a phone
has been turned off

39:59.048 --> 40:02.182
or locked for more than 48 hours
or drained the battery,

40:02.182 --> 40:03.488
it requires a passcode.

40:03.488 --> 40:06.229
This one was off
and locked and dead.

40:06.229 --> 40:08.449
Of course.So the thing basically
is a paperweight.

40:08.449 --> 40:11.539
I could try the two most common
six-digit passcodes --

40:11.539 --> 40:13.367
123456, and...

40:13.367 --> 40:15.195
-654321.
-654321.

40:15.195 --> 40:16.675
For real?

40:16.675 --> 40:19.112
-People have no imagination.
-Go for it.

40:25.118 --> 40:26.989
Oh, man.

40:26.989 --> 40:28.948
-We still have eight tries left.
-And still no insight.

40:28.948 --> 40:30.819
I mean, we don't even know
if it's Billy's phone.

40:30.819 --> 40:33.169
We just know
it was in his possession.I can help you with that.

40:33.169 --> 40:36.434
I could trace the serial number
off the back of the phone

40:36.434 --> 40:38.131
and find out where and when
it was sold.

40:38.131 --> 40:39.785
That's easy.

40:39.785 --> 40:41.090
All right, do it.

40:41.395 --> 40:43.571
No problem.
Hi. Welcome to Chestnut Connect.

40:43.571 --> 40:44.964
-May I help you?
-Hey, Greg.

40:44.964 --> 40:47.314
-You're the manager, yeah?
-I am.

40:47.314 --> 40:49.359
SFPD, Homicide.

40:49.359 --> 40:52.624
We need to know who bought the
phone with this serial number.

40:52.624 --> 40:55.627
Wait, so the woman who called
was telling me the truth?

40:55.627 --> 40:57.672
Sorry, she just didn't
sound like a cop.

40:57.672 --> 40:59.500
Uh...

40:59.500 --> 41:01.850
What does a-a cop sound like?
I'm -- I'm just curious.

41:01.850 --> 41:04.549
Oh, n-- I wasn't, um, saying
that because she's a woman.

41:04.549 --> 41:06.638
Right, right.I mean, personally,
I'm a feminist.

41:06.638 --> 41:08.378
Right, me, too.
How's that serial number coming,

41:08.378 --> 41:10.424
-there, Greg?
-Uh, right.

41:10.424 --> 41:12.731
It's, um -- yeah, no,
I'm just trying to explain

41:12.731 --> 41:15.516
that you can't believe
everyone who calls and
says that they're a cop.

41:15.516 --> 41:19.346
I mean, it could be a-a
pissed-off wife or a girlfriend.

41:19.346 --> 41:20.826
Or, you know, a-a husband.

41:20.826 --> 41:22.392
-Totally, yeah.
-Yeah.

41:22.392 --> 41:24.003
-Mm...
-How we doing?

41:24.003 --> 41:26.658
Oh. Yeah.

41:26.658 --> 41:27.963
Don't stop there, Greg.

41:27.963 --> 41:29.530
Well, it's 1
of the 10 phones

41:29.530 --> 41:33.403
that I sold last Christmas
to Alicia Barnes.

41:43.631 --> 41:46.634
♪♪
